Alexander joined the United States Navy in 1955.
He moved to Oakland, California, in 1957, and began a long history of working with various San Francisco Bay area musicians.
In 1968, he recorded his first songs for the compilation album Oakland Blues, released by World Pacific Records.
He performed at the Ann Arbor Blues and Jazz Festival in 1970 and at the San Francisco Blues Festival many times from 1973 onward.
